Jack's daughter is telling her friends about the story of her father's life: 
(1)Jack started high school 1 year before the first Pulitzer Prizes were announced; 
(2)Jack studied in high school for 3 years; 
(3)Jack started dating 1 year before the first Pulitzer Prizes were announced; 
(4)Jack ended his romantic relationship 11 years after he started university; 
(5)Jack started university 3 years after he started high school; 
(6)Jack graduated from university 4 years before bubble gum was invented; 
(7)Jack started working at a company in 1925; 
(8)Jack got married 13 years after the first Pulitzer Prizes were announced; 
(9)Jack became a father 8 years after he ended his romantic relationship.
____ 41 years after the first Pulitzer Prizes were announced.
A: bubble gum was invented	B: Jack started high school	C: Jack graduated from university	D: Michael Jackson was born

Jack's daughter is telling her friends about the story of her father's life: 
(1)Jack started high school 42 years before Michael Jackson was born; 
(2)Jack graduated from high school 2 years after the first Pulitzer Prizes were announced; 
(3)Jack started dating 53 years before Apollo 11 landed on the moon; 
(4)Jack ended his romantic relationship 11 years after he graduated from high school; 
(5)Jack started university 3 years after he started high school; 
(6)Jack studied in university and spent 5 years on it; 
(7)Jack started working at a company 44 years before Apollo 11 landed on the moon; 
(8)Jack got married 6 years after he graduated from university; 
(9)Jack became a father 31 years before Apollo 11 landed on the moon.
Select the incorrect statement(s): ____
A: Jack graduated from university after he started high school.	B: There is a 56-year gap between Jack started working at a company and IBM released the first personal computer.	C: Jack started dating 1 year before the first Pulitzer Prizes were announced.	D: None of the options above meet the requirements of the question.

Jack's daughter is telling her friends about the story of her father's life: 
(1)Jack started junior high school 68 years before IBM released the first personal computer; 
(2)Jack graduated from junior high school 1 year before the first Pulitzer Prizes were announced; 
(3)Jack met his future wife 2 years after he started junior high school; 
(4)Jack started high school 1 year after he met his future wife; 
(5)Jack graduated from high school 39 years before Michael Jackson was born; 
(6)Jack started dating 29 years before the United Nations was founded; 
(7)Jack was in a romantic relationship and spent 14 years on it; 
(8)Jack started working at a company 9 years after he graduated from junior high school; 
(9)Jack became a father 25 years after he started junior high school.
Select the incorrect statement(s): ____
A: Jack started working at a company after he started junior high school.	B: Jack graduated from junior high school 3 years after he started junior high school.	C: The first Pulitzer Prizes were announced after Jack started junior high school.	D: Jack graduated from high school before he started dating.

小明的女儿正在给朋友讲述父亲的一生: 
(1)他开始上初中是在泡泡糖被发明的15年前; 
(2)他初中毕业是在泡泡糖被发明的12年前; 
(3)在联合国成立的30年之前，他遇见未来的妻子; 
(4)他开始谈恋爱是在泡泡糖被发明的12年前; 
(5)在1930年，他结束谈恋爱; 
(6)他进入公司是在泡泡糖被发明的3年前; 
(7)他结婚的时间比泡泡糖被发明晚2年; 
(8)他退休是在他结婚的34年后。
以下选项中正确的是____
A: 他遇见未来的妻子是在他退休的49年前。	B: IBM发布第一款个人电脑的年份比他退休晚。	C: 他开始谈恋爱的年份比谷歌创立早。	D: 在谷歌创立的17年之前，他开始上初中。

小明是一名大学生，以下是他的每周安排: 
(1)在周一，他学日语; 
(2)周三，他打羽毛球; 
(3)在周三，他开组会; 
(4)在他学日语的3天之后，他阅读科幻小说; 
(5)在他打羽毛球之后2天，他约会; 
(6)在他阅读科幻小说之后3天，他看电影。
以下选项中不正确的是____
A: 在他阅读科幻小说之后6天，他学日语。	B: 在他约会的5天之后，他学日语。	C: 他开组会和他看电影中间差了2天。	D: 在他打羽毛球之前2天，他学日语。
